        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:15AM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 214 AM MDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Scranton, or 9
miles east of Bowman, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowman, Scranton, Reeder, Bucyrus, Gascoyne, Bowman Haley Dam, and
Buffalo Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Persons in campgrounds should seek shelter in a sturdy structure
until this storm passes.</instruction>
